  "texts": [
    "Code2Vec parses a method into an AST, and represents each path between two AST leaves as a vector.",
    "Based on the resulting vectors that represent patches within the AST, Code2Vec represents the whole method as a vector.",
    "A class is presented as a vector that equals the average of the vectors of methods within this class.",
    "The vector of the to-be-tested method and the vector of its potential target class are fed into an SVM-based binary classifier to predict whether the method should be moved to the given target class.",
    "Note that, the deep learning model employed by this approach (i.e., Code2Vec) is unsupervised."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}